Network Resilience Graph¶

In [109]:
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def attack_graph(graph, num_nodes_to_remove):
    attacked_graph = graph.copy()
    nodes_to_remove = np.random.choice(attacked_graph.nodes(), size=num_nodes_to_remove, replace=False)
    attacked_graph.remove_nodes_from(nodes_to_remove)
    return attacked_graph

# Function to plot the network resilience graph
def plot_resilience_graph(graph, num_simulations):
    original_size = len(max(nx.connected_components(graph), key=len))

    # Perform resilience simulations
    results = []
    for i in range(num_simulations):
        attacked_graph = attack_graph(graph, int(len(graph) * 0.1 * i))  # Attack 10% of nodes
        largest_cc_size = len(max(nx.connected_components(attacked_graph), key=len))
        resilience_ratio = largest_cc_size / original_size
        results.append(resilience_ratio)

    # Plot the results
    plt.plot(np.arange(0, num_simulations * 10, 10), results, marker='o')
    plt.title("Network Resilience Graph")
    plt.xlabel("Percentage of Nodes Removed")
    plt.ylabel("Resilience Ratio")
    plt.show()

num_simulations = 10

plot_resilience_graph(G, num_simulations)

Betweenness Centrality Distribution¶

In [175]:
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot_betweenness_centrality(graph):
    betweenness_centrality = nx.betweenness_centrality(graph)
    values = list(betweenness_centrality.values())

    # Plot the distribution
    plt.hist(values, bins=20, alpha=0.7)
    plt.title("Betweenness Centrality Distribution")
    plt.xlabel("Betweenness Centrality")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.show()
# Plot the betweenness centrality distribution
plot_betweenness_centrality(G)

Road Network Correlation Analysis between Roles¶

degree_centrality =list(nx.degree_centrality(G).values())
Closeness_Centrality =list(nx.closeness_centrality(G).values())
betweenness_centrality = list(nx.betweenness_centrality(G).values())
correlation_matrix = pd.DataFrame({
    'Degree Centrality':degree_centrality ,
    'Closeness Centrality':Closeness_Centrality,
    'Betweenness Centrality':betweenness_centrality
})
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".2f", linewidths=.5)
plt.title("Road Network Correlation Analysis between Roles")
plt.show()

import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def attack_graph(graph, num_nodes_to_remove):
    attacked_graph = graph.copy()
    nodes_to_remove = np.random.choice(attacked_graph.nodes(), size=num_nodes_to_remove, replace=False)
    attacked_graph.remove_nodes_from(nodes_to_remove)
    return attacked_graph

# Function to plot the network resilience graph
def plot_resilience_graph(graph, num_simulations):
    original_size = len(max(nx.connected_components(graph), key=len))

    # Perform resilience simulations
    results = []
    for i in range(num_simulations):
        attacked_graph = attack_graph(graph, int(len(graph) * 0.1 * i))  # Attack 10% of nodes
        largest_cc_size = len(max(nx.connected_components(attacked_graph), key=len))
        resilience_ratio = largest_cc_size / original_size
        results.append(resilience_ratio)

    # Plot the results

    plt.title("Network Resilience Graph For Random Network Graph")
    plt.xlabel("Percentage of Nodes Removed")
    plt.ylabel("Resilience Ratio")
    plt.show()

num_simulations = 10

plot_resilience_graph(Gi, num_simulations)
